Rob:

There may yet be another problem to clear up, as well.  My
understanding is the actual authoriative data that the NIC's server
runs from is in DOMAIN:.  Yet there is another file in NETINFO: named
ROOT-SERVERS.TXT, which also has this same information.  I don't know
which is derived from which, or even if either is derived from the
other, but where there is duplicate data, there is bound to be
trouble.  I saw a copy of last week's file, which contained the .ARPA
extensions.  Is anyone using ROOT-SERVERS.TXT to init their cache?

Additionally, it would probably make life easier for all involved if
the authoritative root server supported zone transfer.  That way, the
whole update process could be automated.  But before we see zone
transfers of the root, is there any reason why . has a 30 minute
refresh time?
-- 
Eliot Lear
[lear@net.bio.net]

